510 Project (Worker Productivity)

2022-12-02

Intro to data set

Source: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ishadss/productivity-prediction-of-garment-employees

Variables: 01 date : Date in MM-DD-YYYY 02 day : Day of the Week 03 quarter : A portion of the month. A month was divided into four quarters 04 department : Associated department with the instance 05 teamno : Associated team number with the instance 06 noofworkers : Number of workers in each team 07 noofstylechange : Number of changes in the style of a particular product 08 targetedproductivity : Targeted productivity set by the Authority for each team for each day. 09 smv : Standard Minute Value, it is the allocated time for a task 10 wip : Work in progress. Includes the number of unfinished items for products 11 overtime : Represents the amount of overtime by each team in minutes 12 incentive : Represents the amount of financial incentive (in BDT) that enables or motivates a particular course of action. 13 idletime : The amount of time when the production was interrupted due to several reasons 14 idlemen : The number of workers who were idle due to production interruption 15 actual_productivity : The actual % of productivity that was delivered by the workers. It ranges from 0-1.

Some Questions.

  1. Which department is most productive?
  2. Which day of the week is most productive for each department?
  3. Which team in the sewing department is the most productive?
  4. Does the amount of over time impact the productivity in the sewing department?
  5. Does the amount of incentives impact the productivity in the sewing department?
  6. Does the number of workers impact the productivity in the sewing department?

There are a lot of missing values for wip.

3. Investigate the missing values in wip

work |>
  mutate(is.na.wip = is.na(wip)) |>
  select(department, is.na.wip) |>
  group_by(department, is.na.wip) |>
  summarize(count = n())
## # A tibble: 2  3
## # Groups:   department [2]
##   department is.na.wip count
##   <chr>      <lgl>     <int>
## 1 finishing  TRUE        506
## 2 sweing     FALSE       691

The finishing department always has missing wip values because theytake all the work in progress parts and put them together. The sewing department will always have varying # of wip garments.

4. select important variables and data cleaning

work2 <- work |>
  select(-quarter, -smv, -idle_time, -idle_men, -no_of_style_change) |>
  mutate(department = factor(ifelse(department == "sweing", "sewing", department)))
names(work2)
##  [1] "date"                  "department"            "day"                  
##  [4] "team"                  "targeted_productivity" "wip"                  
##  [7] "over_time"             "incentive"             "no_of_workers"        
## [10] "actual_productivity"
work3 <- work2 |>
  rename(dept = department, target = targeted_productivity, ot = over_time, 
         workers = no_of_workers, actual = actual_productivity) |>
  mutate(dept = factor(dept), team = factor(team), day = factor(day))
